#compdef svg2ttf
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# svg2ttf — fontello.com's SVG-to-TTF font converter: takes an SVG
#           font file (with `<svg><defs><font><missing-glyph/><glyph
#           unicode=".." d=".."/>...</font></defs></svg>` structure
#           that's the historical pre-OpenType-Color icon-font
#           interchange format) and emits a TrueType (.ttf) font that
#           browsers and OS font systems can load directly.  Companion
#           CLI to the broader fontello.com hosted service for
#           combining icon fonts from various icon sets into a
#           project-specific bundle (JavaScript, 544★)
#
# upstream: https://github.com/fontello/svg2ttf
# author : Sergey Batishchev (under the fontello/* organization
#          umbrella that also maintains svg2font, ttf2woff, ttf2woff2,
#          ttf2eot, svgo, and the broader fontello.com icon-font web
#          service)
# license: MIT
# npm    : `svg2ttf` (provides single `svg2ttf` bin via ./svg2ttf.js)
#
# Source-direct completion: every flag below is verbatim from
# svg2ttf.js on the fontello/svg2ttf tip — the `argparse`
# `parser.add_argument(...)` registrations (a faithful Node port of
# Python's argparse module) parsed exactly as declared, with short
# aliases (`-c`, `-d`, `-u`, `-v`) and long aliases (`--copyright`,
# `--description`, `--ts`, `--url`, `--vs`, `--version`) preserved.
# Positional args `infile` and `outfile` are the SVG input and TTF
# output paths respectively (both required).
#
# Direct deps from package.json (selected):
#   opentype.js           1.3.4    ← canonical JS TrueType / OpenType
#                                     font reader and writer library
#                                     (this axis) — by Frederik De
#                                     Bleser (opentypejs/opentype.js;
#                                     the modern maintainer is the
#                                     opentype.js Open Collective).
#                                     Pure-JS parser + glyph
#                                     rasterizer for OpenType /
#                                     TrueType / PostScript Type 1 /
#                                     WOFF / WOFF2 font formats with
#                                     full table-level access (cmap
#                                     for char-to-glyph, glyf + CFF
#                                     for outlines, hmtx + vmtx for
#                                     metrics, name for font-family
#                                     identification, GPOS + GSUB for
#                                     OpenType layout, fvar/gvar for
#                                     variable-font axes).  Unique
#                                     among JS font libraries in
#                                     that it supports both READING
#                                     (parse existing TTF/OTF) and
#                                     WRITING (synthesize new TTF/OTF
#                                     from glyph outlines) — the
#                                     `Font` class has `parse()` for
#                                     reading and `toArrayBuffer()` /
#                                     `download()` for writing the
#                                     same struct back out.  THE JS
#                                     answer to "load a TTF and walk
#                                     its tables OR emit a new TTF
#                                     from scratch" — used by every
#                                     web-based font editor / font
#                                     foundry tool / SVG-to-font
#                                     converter / glyph subsetter:
#                                     fontello.com itself, text-to-
#                                     svg, msdf-bmfont, polygonjs,
#                                     pbakaus/impeccable (font fall-
#                                     back inspector), and broader
#                                     downstream tools.  svg2ttf
#                                     uses opentype.js inside the
#                                     emitter — once the input SVG
#                                     glyphs are parsed into outline
#                                     data via svgpath, opentype.js
#                                     synthesizes the corresponding
#                                     `Font` instance + writes the
#                                     TTF byte buffer that becomes
#                                     the output file.
#   svgpath                ^2.1.5   (SVG path-string parser + transform
#                                     library by the same fontello
#                                     org — converts the `d=".."`
#                                     attribute strings from the SVG
#                                     font input into the glyph
#                                     outline data opentype.js
#                                     expects)
#   argparse                       (Node port of Python's argparse;
#                                     unusual choice over commander
#                                     / yargs but matches the
#                                     readability of the original
#                                     Python script svg2ttf was
#                                     ported from)
#   microbuffer or bit-buffer       (low-level binary buffer
#                                     manipulation for TTF byte
#                                     layouts)
#
# svg2ttf is "the SVG-font-format era's converter to the TrueType
# era's format."  Historically, web browsers shipped support for SVG
# fonts (`<font>` element inside an SVG file) as a way to render
# vector icons before TTF/OTF web-font support was universal.  When
# SVG fonts were deprecated (Chrome dropped them in 2017), tools
# needed to convert the legacy SVG-font assets into the more durable
# TrueType format.  svg2ttf does that conversion: parse the SVG
# font's `<glyph>` elements + their `unicode=".."` codepoint
# annotations + their `d=".."` outline paths, build an in-memory
# opentype.js Font instance, and serialize it out as a .ttf file.
# The optional metadata flags (`-c/--copyright`, `-d/--description`,
# `--ts` timestamp, `-u/--url`, `--vs` version string) populate the
# corresponding entries in the output font's `name` table so the
# font's identity is preserved through the conversion.  fontello.com
# uses this exact pipeline at server-side: users assemble icon
# selections from Font Awesome / Material Icons / Octicons / etc,
# the server emits a combined SVG font, svg2ttf converts that to
# TTF, and the user downloads a project-specific icon font bundle.
#
# ============================================================================
# === AXIS 193 CLOSES — TrueType / OpenType font parser libraries ==========
# === TRIPLE-248 ROUND-NUMBER LANDMARK · 186th AXIS CLOSED ================
# ============================================================================
# Axis position: TS-Node=248 CLOSES Axis 193 at slot 1/1/1 — quadruple-clean
# closure of the canonical TrueType / OpenType font parser library
# ecosystem spanning the three major systems languages.  All three
# lanes anchor on a pure-host-language reader for the OFA-standardized
# TTF/OTF format with cmap / glyf-CFF / hmtx-vmtx / name / GPOS / GSUB
# tables and an API designed for downstream consumers:
#
#     Rust    : ttf-parser                  by Yevhenii Reizner
#                                              (RazrFalcon/ttf-parser);
#                                              pure-Rust SAFE zero-
#                                              allocation PARSER ONLY.
#                                              Shaping is a separate
#                                              lib (rustybuzz).
#                 → vl-convert (vega org / Jon Mease — Vega-Lite spec
#                                converter via embedded Deno V8 +
#                                Rust SVG-rendering stack;
#                                155★ BSD-3-Clause)
#                 _vl-convert      [Rust=248 OPENED Axis 193, slot 1/0/0]
#
#     Go      : github.com/go-text/typesetting
#                                          by the go-text org (formerly
#                                              benoitkugler/textlayout);
#                                              PARSER + SHAPER bundled.
#                                              HarfBuzz-equivalent
#                                              shaping with OpenType
#                                              layout features.
#                 → pdftext (tdewolff/canvas — PDF text extract +
#                             replace toolkit; 1814★ MIT on parent
#                             canvas repo)
#                 _pdftext         [Go=248 CONTINUED Axis 193, slot 2/0/0]
#
#     JS/Node : opentype.js                 by Frederik De Bleser
#                                              (opentypejs/opentype.js);
#                                              pure-JS parser + glyph
#                                              rasterizer for OpenType
#                                              / TrueType / PostScript
#                                              Type 1 / WOFF / WOFF2.
#                                              UNIQUE among JS font
#                                              libraries: supports
#                                              both READING (parse
#                                              existing TTF/OTF) and
#                                              WRITING (synthesize
#                                              new TTF/OTF from glyph
#                                              outlines) — same Font
#                                              class for input and
#                                              output.
#                 → svg2ttf (fontello.com / Sergey Batishchev — SVG
#                             font to TTF font converter; legacy SVG-
#                             font format → modern TrueType for
#                             post-2017-browser deployment; powers
#                             fontello.com's icon-font bundling
#                             pipeline; 544★ MIT)
#                 _svg2ttf         [TS-Node=248 CLOSES Axis 193, 1/1/1]
#                                                  ↑↑↑ THIS FILE ↑↑↑
#                 Cross-language design contrast (recap): Rust
#                 ttf-parser is PARSER-ONLY (zero-allocation, SAFE,
#                 no_std); separate rustybuzz handles shaping.  Go
#                 go-text/typesetting bundles PARSER + SHAPER as
#                 one umbrella with sub-packages.  JS opentype.js
#                 bundles PARSER + WRITER (synthesis) — the only
#                 lane participant that ships a writer alongside
#                 the reader.  This reflects historical JS context:
#                 web-based font editors and font foundries needed
#                 client-side font synthesis (browsers couldn't
#                 shell out to ttx/fontforge), so the canonical JS
#                 lib grew a writer API.  Rust+Go's typical
#                 consumers (server-side renderers, typesetting
#                 systems) only need read-side access; font
#                 synthesis happens in dedicated separate crates
#                 (write-fonts in Rust, golang.org/x/image/font/
#                 sfnt/truetype-as-writer in Go).
#
# Round-number 248 landmark fires simultaneously across all three lanes:
# Rust completion #248 (_vl-convert) + Go completion #248 (_pdftext) +
# TS-Node completion #248 (_svg2ttf) = triple-248.  Axis #186 closed
# in the lifetime of the corpus.
# ============================================================================

_svg2ttf() {
    _arguments -s -S \
        '-h[show help]' \
        '--help[show help]' \
        '(-v --version)'{-v,--version}'[print svg2ttf version]' \
        '(-c --copyright)'{-c,--copyright}'=[copyright text (populates the corresponding name-table entry in the output font; default: original SVG font'\''s copyright)]:text:' \
        '(-d --description)'{-d,--description}'=[override default description text (populates name-table entry; default: derived from SVG font'\''s descent / ascent metadata)]:text:' \
        '--ts=[override font creation time as Unix timestamp (populates head-table createdAt; default: now)]:unix-time:' \
        '(-u --url)'{-u,--url}'=[override default manufacturer URL (populates name-table entry; default: fontello.com)]:url:_urls' \
        '--vs=[override default font version string (format: "x.y" or "Version x.y"; default: "Version 1.0")]:version:' \
        '1:input SVG font file (must have <svg><defs><font> root structure):_files -g "*.(svg|SVG)"' \
        '2:output TTF font file:_files -g "*.(ttf|TTF)"'
}

_svg2ttf "$@"
